  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "No one will go to school tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Tamil Teachers' Association has announced that teachers and principals will not go to school from Monday.",
        "The Ministry of Education has announced how to behave when schools start tomorrow. It is a politics that confuses principals, teachers and students in all schools in Sri Lanka, the Ministry of Education has announced that urban schools should be held for three days and rural schools for five days.",
        "This is a funny thing. Teachers in rural areas are generally from urban areas. There is no transportation route for them. Even public transport buses refuse to transport those teachers as they have no fuel to travel alone.",
        "Telling them to go to school and teach students in this situation is a really bad announcement",
        "The government needs to make it clear that teachers are not in a position to teach students or students are in a position to learn.",
        "It is a firm announcement that none of us will go to school from next Monday until the fuel is settled.",
        "We have made this clear to the Minister of Education, the Secretary to the Minister of Education, the Secretaries of the Ministries of Education in the Provinces, the Directors of the Provinces and the Directors of Zones.",
        "Therefore, we request the Provincial Secretaries, Provincial Directors, Zonal Directors of Education and even the Principals to understand this announcement. (R)"
      ],
